"Ravizza G., Peucker-Ehrenbrink B.","Chemostratigraphic Evidence of Deccan Volcanism from the Marine Osmium Isotope Record",2003,"Science","302","5649",,"1392","1395",,,10.1126/science.1089209,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0345306755&partnerID=40&md5=1b78381e94265acb960a31c9149d66ff","Department of Geology and Geophysics, University of Hawaii, Honolulu, HI 96822-2225, United States; Dept. of Mar. Chem. and Geochemistry, Woods Hole Oceanogr. Inst. (WHOI), Woods Hole, MA 02543, United States","Ravizza, G., Department of Geology and Geophysics, University of Hawaii, Honolulu, HI 96822-2225, United States; Peucker-Ehrenbrink, B., Dept. of Mar. Chem. and Geochemistry, Woods Hole Oceanogr. Inst. (WHOI), Woods Hole, MA 02543, United States","Continental flood basalt (CFB) volcanism is hypothesized to have played a causative rote in global climate change and mass extinctions. Uncertainties associated with radiometric dating preclude a clear chronological assessment of the environmental consequences of CFB volcanism. Our results document a 25% decline in the marine 187Os/188Os record that predates the Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary (KTB) and coincides with late Maastrichtian warming. We argue that this decline provides a chemostratigraphic marker of Deccan volcanism and thus constitutes compelling evidence that the main environmental consequence of Deccan volcanism was a transient global warming event of 3° to 5°C that is fully resolved from the KTB mass extinction.",,"Climatology; Environmental impact; Global warming; Radiometry; Stratigraphy; Volcanoes; Chemostratigraphy; Mass extinction; Basalt; isotope; osmium; chemostratigraphy; flood basalt; global warming; Maastrichtian; mass extinction; osmium isotope; paleoclimate; volcanism; article; chemostatigraphy; cretaceous; documentation; environmental factor; environmental temperature; greenhouse effect; priority journal; recording; species extinction; stratigraphy; tertiary; volcano; warming; Animals; Climate; Geologic Sediments; Greenhouse Effect; Isotopes; Osmium; Population Density; Seawater; Time; Volcanic Eruption; Staphylococcus phage 187",,"osmium, 7440-04-2; Isotopes; Osmium, 7440-04-2",,,,"Courtillot, V.E., Renne, P.R., (2003) C. R. Geosci., 335, p. 113; Wignall, P.B., (2001) Earth Sci. Rev., 53, p. 1; Barrera, E., Savin, S.M., (1999) Geol. Soc. Am. Spec. Pap., 332, p. 245; Li, L., Keller, G., (1999) Mar. Geol., 161, p. 171; Olsson, R.K., Wright, J.D., Miller, K.G., (2001) J. Foram. Res., 31, p. 275; Hofmann, C., Feraud, G., Courtillot, V., (2000) Earth Planet. Sci. Lett., 180, p. 13; Courtillot, V., (2000) Earth Planet. Sci. Lett., 182, p. 137; Cohen, A.S., Coe, A.L., (2002) Geology, 30, p. 267; Peucker-Ehrenbrink, B., Ravizza, G., (2000) Terra Nova, 12, p. 205; McArthur, J.M., Howarth, R.J., Bailey, T.R., (2001) J. Geol., 109, p. 155; Pegram, W.J., Turekian, K.K., (1999) Geochim. Cosmochim. Acta, 63, p. 4053; Warner, T.B., Gieskes, J.H., (1974) Init. Rep. Deep Sea Drill. Proj., 25, p. 395; Zachos, J.C., Arthur, M.A., (1986) Paleoceanography, 1, p. 5; Li, L., Keller, G., (1998) Geology, 26, p. 995; Hassler, D.R., Peucker-Ehrenbrink, B., Ravizza, G.E., (2000) Chem. Geol., 166, p. 1; Hicks, J.F., Johnson, K.R., Obradovich, J.D., Tauxe, L., Clark, D., (2002) Geol. Soc. Am. Spec. Pap., 361, p. 35; Wilf, P., Johnson, K.R., Huber, B.T., (2003) Proc. Nat. Acad. Sci. USA., 100, p. 599; Nordt, L., Atchley, S., Dworkin, S.I., (2002) Geology, 30, p. 703; Vonhof, H.B., Smit, J., (1997) Geology, 25, p. 347; Ravizza, G., Nords, R.N., Blusztajn, J., Aubry, M.P., (2001) Paleoceanography, 16, p. 155; Mukhopadhyay, S., Farley, K.A., Montanari, A., (2001) Geochim. Cosmochim. Acta, 65, p. 653; Allégre, C.J., Birck, J.L., Capmas, F., Courtillot, V., (1999) Earth Planet. Sci. Lett., 170, p. 197; Pande, K., (2002) Proc. Indian Acad. Sci. Earth Planet Sci., 111, p. 115; noteTayLor, A.S., Lasaga, A.C., (1999) Chem. Geol., 161, p. 199; Banerjee, A.C., Raj, D., Roychowdhury, M., (2